  "response": "The amount of human excreta produced by a single person can vary based on several factors, including diet, hydration, and overall health. However, on average:\n\n- A typical adult produces about 100 to 300 grams (approximately 0.22 to 0.66 pounds) of feces per day.\n- In terms of urine, the average adult excretes about 1 to 2 liters (approximately 0.26 to 0.53 gallons) daily.\n\nThese figures can fluctuate significantly depending on individual circumstances, but they provide a general idea of the daily output of human excreta.",
